<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="csrf-token" content={Phoenix.Controller.get_csrf_token()} />
    <title>Localize Playground</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="16x16" href="/favicon-16.png" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="/favicon-32.png" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <link phx-track-static rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/app.css" />
    <%!-- MF2_EDITOR_INTEGRATION: token theme stylesheet

          `mf2_wasm_editor` ships 30 Pygments-ported themes under
          its `priv/themes/`. We pick `monokai` (dark) and link it
          here. The theme styles `.mf2-highlight` + every
          `.mf2-<capture>` span the hook paints (`.mf2-variable`,
          `.mf2-punctuation-bracket`, `.mf2-string-escape`, …).

          Swap `monokai.css` for any of the other 29 names to try
          a different palette. The endpoint only serves the
          whitelisted files — see endpoint.ex.

          Guide: https://hexdocs.pm/mf2_wasm_editor/features.html#themes --%>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/mf2_editor/themes/monokai.css" />
    <%!-- MF2_EDITOR_INTEGRATION: script tag

          `Mf2WasmEditor.script_tags/1` emits a single
          `<script type="module" src="/mf2_editor/mf2_editor.js">`
          tag that loads the LiveView hook. The hook is an ES module
          that imports the web-tree-sitter runtime from a sibling
          file, so there's no separate loader script.

          **Order matters**: the MF2 tag must come BEFORE app.js.
          ES modules are deferred by default and evaluate in
          document order, matching the explicit `defer` on app.js.
          app.js constructs the LiveSocket and reads
          `window.Mf2WasmEditor.Hooks` at that moment; this
          script must have evaluated first to populate it.
          Put them the wrong way round and the hook silently
          never mounts — the editor accepts keystrokes but never
          paints.

          Guide: https://hexdocs.pm/mf2_wasm_editor/wiring.html#2-emit-the-script-tags-in-the-root-layout --%>
    {raw(Mf2WasmEditor.script_tags())}
    <script defer phx-track-static type="text/javascript" src="/assets/app.js">
    </script>
  </head>
  <body>
    {@inner_content}
  </body>
</html>
